{
  "doc_id": "12753",
  "text": "A famous result by Welch [CITATION_1] provides a universal lower bound on the mean and maximum value of powers of absolute values of inner products (a.k.a cross-correlations) of frame vectors. Frames which achieve the Welch lower bound on maximal absolute cross-correlation are known as equiangular tight frames (ETF).",
